                 male-female comparisons than in female-female comparisons,
                 consistent with observed differences in dispersal propensity
                 between the sexes. Using the pedigree, we demonstrated how
                 various genealogical relationships contribute to fine-scale
                 isolation-by-distance. Simulations using field-observed
                 distributions of male and female natal dispersal distances
                 showed good agreement with the distribution of geographic
                 distances between breeding individuals of different pedigree
                 relationship classes. Furthermore, we built coalescent
                 simulations parameterized by the observed dispersal curve,
                 population density, and immigration rate, and showed how
